title: Modified GC so deleted data can be dropped #559
body:
The Oracle is now the autority on GC.  The Oracle looks in Zookeeper to
determine the oldest active timestamp for all transactors.   After finding the
oldest active timestamp if persist this in zookeeper for use by garbage
collection iterators.  The Oracle also returns the GC timestamp it persisted to
Zookeeper to any clients that request a timestamp.  Clients use this GC time
from the oracle when committing or closing a snapshot to detemine if they
possibly read stale data.
